trans-unit.source: Lookup plugins allow access to outside data sources. Like all templating, these plugins are evaluated on the Ansible control machine, and can include reading the filesystem as well as contacting external datastores and services. trans-unit.source: Lookup plugins are an Ansible-specific extension to the Jinja2 templating language. You can use lookup plugins to access data from outside sources (files, databases, key/value stores, APIs, and other services) within your playbooks. Like all templating, lookups execute and are evaluated on the Ansible control machine. Ansible makes the data returned by a lookup plugin available using the standard templating system. You can use lookup plugins to load variables or templates with information from external sources.

You can use lookup plugins to access data from outside sources (files, databases, key/value stores, APIs, and other services) within your playbooks. You can use lookup plugins to load variables or templates with information from external sources.

trans-unit.source: Lookup plugins are an advanced feature; to best leverage them you should have a good working knowledge of how to use Ansible plays.

trans-unit.source: Lookup plugins can be used anywhere you can use templating in Ansible: in a play, in variables file, or in a Jinja2 template for the template module.
trans-unit.target: Lookupプラグインは、Ansibleでテンプレートを使用できる場所ならどこでも使用できます：プレイ、変数ファイル、またはテンプレートモジュールのJinja2テンプレート。

trans-unit.source: Lookup plugins retrieve data from outside sources such as files, databases, key/value stores, APIs, and other services. Starting with Ansible 2.5, lookups are used more explicitly as part of Jinja2 expressions fed into the loop keyword.
